lead_paragraph: The administration said 11.3 million people had signed up for health insurance so far in the third open enrollment period, citing “unprecedented demand for marketplace coverage.”

abstract: Obama administration reports 11.3 million people have signed up for health insurance so far in Affordable Care Act's third open enrollment period; officials say data about enrollments reveals unprecedented demand for insurance coverage acquired through federal insurance marketplace.
